articles.author: Parisa Hafezi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel hit back at Iran early on Saturday, with its military saying it was conducting strikes against military targets in response to Tehran's attacks on Israel.
articles.title: Israel hits back at Iran with strikes on military targets, IDF says

articles.author: Stephanie Kelly, Andrea Shalal, Alexandra Ulmer
articles.description: Michelle Obama, in her first public campaign event of this U.S. election, will join Democratic presidential nominee Kamala Harris in Michigan on Saturday, while Republican candidate Donald Trump holds his own rally in the battleground state.
articles.title: Michelle Obama, Harris and Trump campaign in Michigan on Saturday

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt, Gabriella Borter, Georgina Mccartney
articles.description: Kamala Harris and Donald Trump took a detour from barnstorming the battleground states that will decide November's election with Friday stops in Texas, a conservative state that was the first to implement a near-total abortion ban.
articles.title: Harris focuses on abortion in Texas, as Trump heads to Michigan

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Commonwealth members selected Shirley Ayorkor Botchwey as secretary-general of the 56-nation club headed by Britain's King Charles, the Commonwealth said on Saturday, the final day of a summit in Samoa attended by Charles and Queen Camilla.
articles.title: Commonwealth selects Shirley Ayorkor Botchwey as new secretary-general

articles.author: Special Reports
articles.description: Members of the last generation to live under unabashed Jim Crow are among voters in a historic presidential election that has been roiled by racial and other divisions.
articles.title: Sixty years after the unwinding of Jim Crow, a historic US election

articles.author: Mike Stone, Ben Blanchard
articles.description: China has been stepping up military pressure against Taiwan, including holding a new round of war games around the island last week.
articles.title: US approves $2 billion arms sale to Taiwan including Ukraine tested missile system

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Russian drone struck a multi-storey residential building in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv on Friday evening, triggering a fire in the top floors and killing one person and injuring five, officials said.
articles.title: Russian drone hits Kyiv high-rise building, kills one, injures five

articles.author: Felix Light, Lucy Papachristou
articles.description: Georgians vote on Saturday in a parliamentary election depicted by both sides as an existential battle that will determine whether the country integrates closely with the West or leans back towards Moscow.
articles.title: Georgia votes in election seen as stark choice between Russia and West

articles.author: Michael Holden
articles.description: Right-wing, anti-immigrant protesters and opposing anti-racism demonstrators are both planning large rallies in London on Saturday, closely watched by a beefed up police operation aimed at heading off any clashes between the rival gatherings.
articles.title: Police gear up for large, rival London protests

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: More than 180,000 people celebrated LGBTQ+ equality and diversity in Taipei on Saturday at east Asia's largest Pride march, joined by Taiwan Vice President Hsiao Bi-khim and the reigning queen of RuPaul's Drag Race, Nymphia Wind.
articles.title: Taiwan vice president, Drag Race winner join big crowds at east Asia's largest Pride march
